1
00:00:18,470 --> 00:00:21,681
‐ Please, Age, come back.

2
00:00:24,768 --> 00:00:27,687
MAN: Did you hear?
The Nodos left the "Argonaut."

3
00:00:27,687 --> 00:00:30,231
MAN: Yeah, and now those
brothers are going to use it

4
00:00:30,231 --> 00:00:33,193
to take credit for
all the princess' hard work.

5
00:00:34,402 --> 00:00:37,405
<i>["Gravitation" by Angela]</i>

6
00:00:37,405 --> 00:00:40,492
[woman singing in Japanese]

7
00:00:40,492 --> 00:00:47,499
<i>♪ ♪</i>

8
00:02:08,163 --> 00:02:09,289
MAIL: I don't hear anything.

9
00:02:09,289 --> 00:02:10,915
TAIL: Maybe she's meditating.

10
00:02:12,042 --> 00:02:14,127
‐ Why is Age
being so mean to her?

11
00:02:14,127 --> 00:02:17,047
I never would've thought
that he could be such a jerk.

12
00:02:17,047 --> 00:02:19,632
‐ Since we left port,
she's pretty much locked herself

13
00:02:19,632 --> 00:02:21,885
in her room,
and the ship's records indicate

14
00:02:21,885 --> 00:02:23,845
she's barely eaten anything.

15
00:02:23,845 --> 00:02:25,680
I'm so worried about her.

16
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:28,099
ANEASHA: Stop talking
about Age like that.

17
00:02:28,099 --> 00:02:30,018
MAIL: But they left.

18
00:02:30,018 --> 00:02:31,853
ANEASHA: Do either of you
really believe

19
00:02:31,853 --> 00:02:34,314
that Age would just abandon
all of us on whim?

20
00:02:34,314 --> 00:02:36,149
[both sigh]

21
00:02:36,149 --> 00:02:37,108
‐ [sighs]

22
00:02:37,108 --> 00:02:38,485
Think about it.

23
00:02:38,485 --> 00:02:41,988
Age had to leave in order
to protect the princess.

24
00:02:41,988 --> 00:02:43,907
BOTH: Protect?
‐ Of course.

25
00:02:43,907 --> 00:02:47,285
From now on, Age will be
a priority target for the enemy.

26
00:02:47,285 --> 00:02:50,914
If he stayed, he'd only
be endangering her life.

27
00:02:50,914 --> 00:02:52,916
At least I think
that's why he left.

28
00:02:52,916 --> 00:02:54,375
‐ I get it.

29
00:02:54,375 --> 00:02:56,586
‐ Well, he should've told
all of that to her.

30
00:02:56,586 --> 00:02:59,214
‐ Looks like Age
really is a jerk.

31
00:02:59,214 --> 00:03:00,423
‐ What was that about Age?

32
00:03:00,423 --> 00:03:02,217
Is he all right?

33
00:03:02,217 --> 00:03:04,302
‐ It's time for your meal,
Princess.

34
00:03:04,302 --> 00:03:05,553
‐ Oh, thank you.

35
00:03:05,553 --> 00:03:08,223
We have a most difficult journey
ahead of us.

36
00:03:08,223 --> 00:03:10,892
It's important for all of us
to keep up our strength.

37
00:03:10,892 --> 00:03:13,728
Leave it there on the table
if you would, Aneasha.

38
00:03:13,728 --> 00:03:15,271
ANEASHA: Yes, Your Highness.

39
00:03:15,271 --> 00:03:16,231
Excuse me.

40
00:03:16,231 --> 00:03:19,359
<i>[soft instrumental music]</i>

41
00:03:19,359 --> 00:03:21,152
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42
00:03:21,152 --> 00:03:23,196
‐ How bizarre.
She's acting fine.

43
00:03:23,196 --> 00:03:26,533
‐ I guess she finally got over
all that stuff with Age.

44
00:03:26,533 --> 00:03:28,493
‐ You two should know better
than that.

45
00:03:28,493 --> 00:03:30,119
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46
00:03:30,119 --> 00:03:33,998
DHIANEILA: I mustn't worry them
any more than I already have.

47
00:03:33,998 --> 00:03:38,044
Now more than ever they'll need
me to be their anchor.

48
00:03:38,044 --> 00:03:44,592
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49
00:03:44,592 --> 00:03:46,010
‐ Really?

50
00:03:46,010 --> 00:03:47,929
So you believe there's
a reason that Age left?

51
00:03:47,929 --> 00:03:50,306
‐ From what I know of the boy,
I'd say there's a good reason

52
00:03:50,306 --> 00:03:51,266
that he left.

53
00:03:51,266 --> 00:03:52,767
‐ Mm.
I see.

54
00:03:52,767 --> 00:03:54,978
You're saying that he intends
to draw enemy fire

55
00:03:54,978 --> 00:03:56,771
in order to protect
the princess.

56
00:03:56,771 --> 00:04:00,275
‐ Beyond that, I see no other
motive for Age to leave us.

57
00:04:00,275 --> 00:04:02,735
The funny thing is
that little monkey doesn't know

58
00:04:02,735 --> 00:04:05,029
what a hero he really is.

59
00:04:05,029 --> 00:04:08,449
IOLAOUS: Captain,
permission to speak freely.

60
00:04:08,449 --> 00:04:10,243
‐ Sure.
Why so formal?

61
00:04:10,243 --> 00:04:11,703
‐ Those brothers.

62
00:04:11,703 --> 00:04:14,706
Is it wise to let the Yunos
family lead the fleet?

63
00:04:14,706 --> 00:04:16,416
‐ [sighs]
IOLAOUS: We shouldn't entrust

64
00:04:16,416 --> 00:04:18,418
humanity's future with them.

65
00:04:18,418 --> 00:04:20,169
It's suicide!

66
00:04:20,169 --> 00:04:22,213
‐ That was
the Council's decision.

67
00:04:22,213 --> 00:04:25,466
In any event, do you know of
anyone better suited

68
00:04:25,466 --> 00:04:28,344
to be trusted with such
a monumental task?

69
00:04:28,344 --> 00:04:29,304
‐ I do.

70
00:04:29,304 --> 00:04:31,472
Princess Dhianeila.

71
00:04:31,472 --> 00:04:34,350
‐ The princess belongs
to the Yunos family too.

72
00:04:34,350 --> 00:04:36,561
‐ She's nothing like them,
and you know it,

73
00:04:36,561 --> 00:04:38,813
not to mention her special bond
with a Nodos.

74
00:04:38,813 --> 00:04:41,065
It would give its own life
to protect her.

75
00:04:41,065 --> 00:04:44,360
She's by far
the most qualified to lead.

76
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:47,030
‐ All I'm going to say
is no comment,

77
00:04:47,030 --> 00:04:50,116
and I say that
as a loyal soldier.

78
00:04:50,116 --> 00:04:52,327
But speaking as your father,

79
00:04:52,327 --> 00:04:53,369
I must agree.

80
00:04:54,829 --> 00:04:57,040
‐ Thank you, Captain.

81
00:05:00,501 --> 00:05:02,003
‐ Do something for me, Bee:

82
00:05:02,003 --> 00:05:05,590
establish a secure comm link
with Nilval on the "Althaia."

83
00:05:05,590 --> 00:05:08,635
It's critical that no one else
in the fleet detects it.

84
00:05:08,635 --> 00:05:10,136
Can you do that?

85
00:05:10,136 --> 00:05:13,473
‐ I can have a secure line
ready for you in one hour.

86
00:05:13,473 --> 00:05:15,099
‐ Then what are you waiting for?

87
00:05:15,099 --> 00:05:16,142
‐ Yes, sir.

88
00:05:17,185 --> 00:05:19,187
‐ I've got no time to lose.

89
00:05:20,855 --> 00:05:23,900
[whooshing]

90
00:05:26,527 --> 00:05:28,905
MELEAGROS:
Descendants of humanity,

91
00:05:28,905 --> 00:05:31,866
long ago our ancestors set forth
on a journey

92
00:05:31,866 --> 00:05:35,411
to explore the infinite
possibilities of this galaxy.

93
00:05:35,411 --> 00:05:39,249
One cannot imagine the hardships
endured by those brave souls

94
00:05:39,249 --> 00:05:41,376
in building our future.

95
00:05:41,376 --> 00:05:44,879
Our great ancestors suffered
so that we might thrive!

96
00:05:44,879 --> 00:05:48,549
The Silver Tribe intends
to dishonor their memory

97
00:05:48,549 --> 00:05:50,718
and to destroy us all.

98
00:05:50,718 --> 00:05:54,013
Now is the time for mankind
to rise.

99
00:05:54,013 --> 00:05:55,807
We must reclaim
our mother planet

100
00:05:55,807 --> 00:05:58,768
from the ruthless
and insatiable Silver Tribe!

101
00:05:58,768 --> 00:06:01,271
Then they shall know
we will never submit

102
00:06:01,271 --> 00:06:03,064
to our murderous oppressors.

103
00:06:03,064 --> 00:06:06,442
Make no mistake:
this is a holy war!

104
00:06:06,442 --> 00:06:09,070
All of humanity,
as well as each of our allies,

105
00:06:09,070 --> 00:06:10,446
must come together.

106
00:06:10,446 --> 00:06:13,741
By working as one,
we shall overcome our foe.

107
00:06:13,741 --> 00:06:15,451
<i>[rousing music]</i>

108
00:06:15,451 --> 00:06:17,245
WOMAN: We are disappointed
to report that materials

109
00:06:17,245 --> 00:06:19,914
and supplies belonging
to the star system were taken

110
00:06:19,914 --> 00:06:21,582
in such a forceful manner.

111
00:06:21,582 --> 00:06:24,252
‐ This doesn't feel
like an allegiance at all.

112
00:06:24,252 --> 00:06:26,170
It feels more like we're being
put under the boot

113
00:06:26,170 --> 00:06:27,630
of the royal family.

114
00:06:27,630 --> 00:06:30,258
‐ I hope you'll accept
my deepest apologies

115
00:06:30,258 --> 00:06:33,928
for my brothers' aggressive
behavior.

116
00:06:33,928 --> 00:06:37,098
The future of humankind
is at stake in this conflict.

117
00:06:37,098 --> 00:06:39,851
We have no other option
but victory.

118
00:06:39,851 --> 00:06:42,812
In order for that to happen,
it is of the utmost importance

119
00:06:42,812 --> 00:06:44,939
that all of the planets
work together,

120
00:06:44,939 --> 00:06:49,152
but all will be lost unless
we forge an alliance of respect.

121
00:06:49,152 --> 00:06:51,362
You shall have my assistance
in this endeavor.

122
00:06:51,362 --> 00:06:55,116
Instead of leading, I shall work
to strengthen our solidarity.

123
00:06:55,116 --> 00:06:57,785
I solemnly swear to you
that this alliance

124
00:06:57,785 --> 00:07:01,289
will never bring about a system
based on fear and mistrust.

125
00:07:01,289 --> 00:07:02,832
WOMAN: Once we confront
the Silver Tribe,

126
00:07:02,832 --> 00:07:04,292
we won't have
the luxury of ignoring

127
00:07:04,292 --> 00:07:06,044
another star system's troubles.

128
00:07:06,044 --> 00:07:08,796
We'll be in it together
until the very end.

129
00:07:08,796 --> 00:07:11,924
MAN: If I may be so bold:
I can say with certainty

130
00:07:11,924 --> 00:07:14,761
that I am not alone in my wish
that you were in command

131
00:07:14,761 --> 00:07:16,471
of the alliance,
Your Highness.

132
00:07:16,471 --> 00:07:18,890
‐ Thank you for your kind words.

133
00:07:21,684 --> 00:07:24,145
NILVAL: It's impossible
to predict how many anthills

134
00:07:24,145 --> 00:07:26,064
there will be or what formation
they'll take.

135
00:07:26,064 --> 00:07:28,941
That means a flexible
but well‐coordianted response

136
00:07:28,941 --> 00:07:30,026
will be the key.

137
00:07:30,026 --> 00:07:31,110
Now, in this scenario‐‐

138
00:07:31,110 --> 00:07:33,237
ATALANTES: [clears throat]

139
00:07:33,237 --> 00:07:36,282
That'll be all, Colonel‐‐
oh, I'm sorry.

140
00:07:36,282 --> 00:07:38,826
I suppose now it's
Lieutenant General Nilval.

141
00:07:38,826 --> 00:07:40,995
[all chuckling]

142
00:07:40,995 --> 00:07:43,956
My Quental Unit will take
the lead in this battle.

143
00:07:43,956 --> 00:07:46,667
We'll blow the enemy
out of the sky.

144
00:07:46,667 --> 00:07:47,877
‐ A reckless plan.

145
00:07:47,877 --> 00:07:49,378
‐ See, that's the thing.

146
00:07:49,378 --> 00:07:51,506
It isn't reckless
because that entire unit

147
00:07:51,506 --> 00:07:53,257
is made up of elite soldiers.

148
00:07:53,257 --> 00:07:56,636
A few worms won't pose
the slightest problem to them.

149
00:07:56,636 --> 00:07:58,513
NILVAL: Then please,
share with us the basic

150
00:07:58,513 --> 00:08:01,099
battle strategies
of the Calydonian Fleet.

151
00:08:01,099 --> 00:08:02,809
‐ I believe I just did.

152
00:08:02,809 --> 00:08:04,852
Besides, we have the Nodos
on our side.

153
00:08:04,852 --> 00:08:07,355
‐ And what if the enemy Nodos
shows up?

154
00:08:07,355 --> 00:08:09,065
ATALANTES: Then our Nodos
will destroy it.

155
00:08:09,065 --> 00:08:11,859
‐ You're going to use the Nodos
as the primary force?

156
00:08:11,859 --> 00:08:13,528
I can't believe
you would let our fate rest

157
00:08:13,528 --> 00:08:15,154
with one individual.

158
00:08:15,154 --> 00:08:18,866
‐ Nilval, I was truly impressed
with the efforts you displayed

159
00:08:18,866 --> 00:08:20,368
on the Huelgoat.

160
00:08:20,368 --> 00:08:22,829
Because of your distinguished
record, you were promoted

161
00:08:22,829 --> 00:08:25,039
to the rank of lieutenant
general and invited to serve

162
00:08:25,039 --> 00:08:26,374
in our fleet.

163
00:08:26,374 --> 00:08:28,251
Now you're an assistant
to the commander.

164
00:08:28,251 --> 00:08:29,877
NILVAL: It's an honor to serve,
sir.

165
00:08:29,877 --> 00:08:31,504
MELEAGROS: Very good.

166
00:08:31,504 --> 00:08:34,048
You will support Atalantes
with everything you've got.

167
00:08:34,048 --> 00:08:35,842
Understood?

168
00:08:35,842 --> 00:08:38,094
‐ Yes, sir, I understand.

169
00:08:40,054 --> 00:08:41,556
We will never achieve victory

170
00:08:41,556 --> 00:08:43,391
playing along with people
like that.

171
00:08:43,391 --> 00:08:45,893
Those monkeys in there
haven't the vaguest idea

172
00:08:45,893 --> 00:08:47,061
what we're up against.

173
00:08:47,061 --> 00:08:49,021
‐ Ma'am.

174
00:08:49,021 --> 00:08:50,106
AGE: Nilval!

175
00:08:50,106 --> 00:08:51,065
‐ Huh?

176
00:08:51,065 --> 00:08:53,234
AGE: [grunting]

177
00:08:53,234 --> 00:08:55,528
‐ Speaking of monkeys,
here comes one now.

178
00:08:55,528 --> 00:08:58,906
‐ Yes, but this monkey's going
to save all of humanity.

179
00:08:58,906 --> 00:09:00,283
Hello there, Mr. Savior.

180
00:09:00,283 --> 00:09:01,993
How can I help you?

181
00:09:01,993 --> 00:09:03,953
‐ Paint.

182
00:09:15,256 --> 00:09:18,259
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

183
00:09:18,259 --> 00:09:22,722
<i>♪ ♪</i>

184
00:09:30,188 --> 00:09:31,939
ROM: Let us begin.

185
00:09:33,191 --> 00:09:36,110
PROME: The fifth Nodos
and the Iron Tribe,

186
00:09:36,110 --> 00:09:39,572
about their existence
and what we can do about it.

187
00:09:41,157 --> 00:09:43,951
ANEASHA: Representatives
of the Orion and Colonis systems

188
00:09:43,951 --> 00:09:45,161
have contacted us.

189
00:09:45,161 --> 00:09:46,787
Even the LMC responded.

190
00:09:46,787 --> 00:09:50,041
And look: we're getting symbols
of friendship from planets

191
00:09:50,041 --> 00:09:51,334
all over the galaxy.

192
00:09:51,334 --> 00:09:53,085
This is just a few of them.

193
00:09:53,085 --> 00:09:54,545
‐ They've given so much.

194
00:09:54,545 --> 00:09:56,255
‐ It's not
just valuables either.

195
00:09:56,255 --> 00:09:59,800
Every loading dock is filled
with small ships and supplies.

196
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,677
A stunning display of support.

197
00:10:01,677 --> 00:10:03,971
Even planets behind enemy lines
have responded

198
00:10:03,971 --> 00:10:05,389
to your initiative.

199
00:10:05,389 --> 00:10:08,476
‐ Please send my sincere thanks
to all who contributed.

200
00:10:08,476 --> 00:10:11,103
I'm going to give the gifts
I've received to the soldiers

201
00:10:11,103 --> 00:10:13,314
as rewards for
all of their hard work.

202
00:10:13,314 --> 00:10:16,150
‐ The princess
is so very generous.

203
00:10:16,150 --> 00:10:19,487
‐ The gifts are because
of the war they know is coming.

204
00:10:19,487 --> 00:10:22,365
It's inevitable.

205
00:10:22,365 --> 00:10:24,075
ANEASHA: You might be mistaken.

206
00:10:24,075 --> 00:10:26,494
I think they're sending gifts
because they believe in you.

207
00:10:26,494 --> 00:10:29,413
Not only did you discover
a path to the starway,

208
00:10:29,413 --> 00:10:31,874
you found the Nodos.

209
00:10:35,002 --> 00:10:36,254
Just look at you.

210
00:10:36,254 --> 00:10:39,382
You should get some rest,
Princess.

211
00:10:41,676 --> 00:10:43,177
NILVAL: Very clever.

212
00:10:43,177 --> 00:10:45,680
I never would've thought
of embedding a secure link

213
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:48,182
in the fleet's own
identification signals.

214
00:10:48,182 --> 00:10:49,892
‐ I can't take all the credit.

215
00:10:49,892 --> 00:10:53,729
The ship's AI unit, Bee No Bee,
came up with that one.

216
00:10:53,729 --> 00:10:57,775
So about this plan
for fleet reorganization.

217
00:10:57,775 --> 00:10:59,569
NILVAL: I've already sent
you the data.

218
00:10:59,569 --> 00:11:01,028
MOBEEDO: Bringing it up now.

219
00:11:01,028 --> 00:11:02,697
‐ Those two should be deposed.

220
00:11:02,697 --> 00:11:06,075
I would do it myself if I were
up to the task of leading.

221
00:11:06,075 --> 00:11:09,036
Unfortunately, I've come
to grips with the reality

222
00:11:09,036 --> 00:11:10,705
that I'm not cut out for that.

223
00:11:10,705 --> 00:11:13,457
Frankly, I think your princess
would be the best choice.

224
00:11:13,457 --> 00:11:16,794
‐ Quite a few people share
precisely that opinion.

225
00:11:16,794 --> 00:11:20,131
But Her Highness is still
very young, and she's withdrawn

226
00:11:20,131 --> 00:11:24,051
from leadership roles so that
her brothers may take over.

227
00:11:24,051 --> 00:11:26,762
NILVAL: We can't afford
to sit back and do nothing.

228
00:11:26,762 --> 00:11:28,889
‐ We'll prepare just in case.

229
00:11:28,889 --> 00:11:32,268
By the way, I've been wondering
about our little monkey.

230
00:11:32,268 --> 00:11:33,686
Is Age all right?

231
00:11:33,686 --> 00:11:35,563
‐ Well, Age is...

232
00:11:35,563 --> 00:11:37,398
he's‐‐he's painting.

233
00:11:37,398 --> 00:11:40,401
AGE: [grunting]

234
00:11:40,401 --> 00:11:42,236
<i>[quirky music]</i>

235
00:11:42,236 --> 00:11:45,239
[laughing]

236
00:11:45,239 --> 00:11:46,782
<i>♪ ♪</i>

237
00:11:46,782 --> 00:11:49,160
[explosions]

238
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:51,287
[lasers firing]

239
00:11:51,287 --> 00:11:52,330
[electronic beeping]

240
00:11:52,330 --> 00:11:53,331
‐ [grunts]

241
00:11:53,331 --> 00:11:55,666
[lasers firing]

242
00:11:56,584 --> 00:11:59,629
[electronic beeping]

243
00:11:59,629 --> 00:12:01,088
[lasers firing]

244
00:12:04,050 --> 00:12:08,095
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
Enemy units remaining: zero.

245
00:12:08,095 --> 00:12:10,598
‐ All units return
to the "Argonaut."

246
00:12:10,598 --> 00:12:12,099
[electric whirring]

247
00:12:12,099 --> 00:12:15,144
[whooshing]

248
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:21,692
Everyone's response time
is dropping.

249
00:12:21,692 --> 00:12:24,236
Time away from battle
has made you sluggish.

250
00:12:24,236 --> 00:12:27,448
Make sure you remedy that before
the next training session.

251
00:12:27,448 --> 00:12:28,449
Dismissed.

252
00:12:28,449 --> 00:12:29,617
ALL: Sir.

253
00:12:32,953 --> 00:12:34,955
ANEASHA: Are you always
that strict?

254
00:12:34,955 --> 00:12:36,040
‐ Hm?

255
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:38,042
I want them at their best,
right?

256
00:12:38,042 --> 00:12:39,585
‐ We're just rear support now.

257
00:12:39,585 --> 00:12:42,338
Is being so demanding
really necessary?

258
00:12:42,338 --> 00:12:45,049
Why don't you relax a little?

259
00:12:45,049 --> 00:12:48,469
‐ Age is always ready for
battle, and we should be too.

260
00:12:48,469 --> 00:12:50,346
The thing about him
is that he never dwells

261
00:12:50,346 --> 00:12:52,098
on his own greatness.

262
00:12:52,098 --> 00:12:55,142
He's humble, and that's what
allowed him to keep fighting

263
00:12:55,142 --> 00:12:57,395
for hundreds of hours on end.

264
00:12:57,395 --> 00:13:00,189
‐ Iolaous,
don't compete with it.

265
00:13:00,189 --> 00:13:01,315
‐ With "it"?

266
00:13:01,315 --> 00:13:02,858
I'm not.
I can't.

267
00:13:02,858 --> 00:13:05,861
I‐‐I'm competing with Age
and the fighting spirit

268
00:13:05,861 --> 00:13:09,031
that he has come to symbolize.

269
00:13:09,031 --> 00:13:11,617
But I suppose that's not
a big deal to you.

270
00:13:11,617 --> 00:13:14,370
‐ Come on.
You know that's not how it is.

271
00:13:14,370 --> 00:13:17,623
I guess I'll go ahead
and leave you to your training.

272
00:13:17,623 --> 00:13:19,166
‐ Thanks for this.

273
00:13:19,166 --> 00:13:20,459
ANEASHA: Any time.

274
00:13:24,422 --> 00:13:31,178
<i>♪ ♪</i>

275
00:13:31,178 --> 00:13:34,432
‐ I thought he'd be drawing
something more cheerful.

276
00:13:34,432 --> 00:13:36,642
But that's kind of creepy.

277
00:13:36,642 --> 00:13:37,643
‐ It's dark.

278
00:13:37,643 --> 00:13:39,228
What is it, anyway?

279
00:13:39,228 --> 00:13:41,772
AGE: A story I heard from Dad
and the others.

280
00:13:41,772 --> 00:13:43,315
‐ Dad and the others?

281
00:13:43,315 --> 00:13:47,361
AGE: Dhianeila calls them
the Golden Tribe.

282
00:13:47,361 --> 00:13:48,863
‐ Golden Tribe?

283
00:13:48,863 --> 00:13:50,030
‐ You mean...

284
00:13:50,030 --> 00:13:54,869
<i>♪ ♪</i>

285
00:13:54,869 --> 00:13:56,412
‐ Star.

286
00:13:56,412 --> 00:13:58,622
‐ I get it.
You see?

287
00:13:58,622 --> 00:14:01,000
It's the fiery demise
of the Silver Tribe.

288
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,418
‐ Yes, I see.

289
00:14:02,418 --> 00:14:05,254
The boy's picture has suddenly
become quite clear.

290
00:14:05,254 --> 00:14:07,673
It is the doom of our enemies.

291
00:14:07,673 --> 00:14:09,341
‐ We can use this picture.

292
00:14:09,341 --> 00:14:10,301
Trust me.

293
00:14:10,301 --> 00:14:11,802
‐ Use?
But how?

294
00:14:11,802 --> 00:14:13,637
‐ The fact that the boy
is drawing this

295
00:14:13,637 --> 00:14:15,389
proves that the Golden Tribe
predicted

296
00:14:15,389 --> 00:14:16,891
our triumphant victory.

297
00:14:16,891 --> 00:14:19,143
We are definitely going
to send this picture

298
00:14:19,143 --> 00:14:20,644
down to the PR department.

299
00:14:20,644 --> 00:14:21,896
‐ Hmm.

300
00:14:21,896 --> 00:14:23,439
You think that
after seeing this picture

301
00:14:23,439 --> 00:14:26,275
everyone will be more interested
in joining our cause.

302
00:14:26,275 --> 00:14:27,818
You're brilliant.

303
00:14:27,818 --> 00:14:29,361
It must be genetic.

304
00:14:29,361 --> 00:14:30,821
[both laugh]

305
00:14:30,821 --> 00:14:31,947
‐ Huh?

306
00:14:31,947 --> 00:14:34,074
‐ We want you
to keep on drawing.

307
00:14:34,074 --> 00:14:36,368
And when it's finished,
we shall donate it

308
00:14:36,368 --> 00:14:39,497
to those under the flag
of the Yunos royal family.

309
00:14:39,497 --> 00:14:42,666
‐ Nilval, you are in charge
of this picture.

310
00:14:42,666 --> 00:14:46,086
He is to have access to
all the materials that he needs.

311
00:14:48,172 --> 00:14:50,216
‐ Put in charge of a picture.

312
00:14:50,216 --> 00:14:52,510
All of
their interpretations aside,

313
00:14:52,510 --> 00:14:54,053
what does this picture mean?

314
00:14:54,053 --> 00:14:56,764
AGE: Future.
NILVAL: Whose future?

315
00:14:56,764 --> 00:14:59,183
AGE: It's the place
where Age is going.

316
00:15:00,601 --> 00:15:01,477
‐ The light,

317
00:15:01,477 --> 00:15:02,770
what does that mean?

318
00:15:05,022 --> 00:15:07,525
AGE: Dhianeila.

319
00:15:07,525 --> 00:15:11,070
Because Dhianelia is the light
that finds everyone's path,

320
00:15:11,070 --> 00:15:13,572
even in the dark sky.

321
00:15:13,572 --> 00:15:15,741
NILVAL: You wanted to protect
this light that shines

322
00:15:15,741 --> 00:15:17,284
even in destruction.

323
00:15:17,284 --> 00:15:20,329
That's why you left
the "Argonaut," isn't it?

324
00:15:20,329 --> 00:15:22,081
AGE: It isn't safe
to be with Age.

325
00:15:22,081 --> 00:15:25,960
‐ This bright light, do you know
when it will lead all of us?

326
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:27,169
AGE: When a star dies.

327
00:15:27,169 --> 00:15:28,128
‐ What?

328
00:15:28,128 --> 00:15:30,631
‐ A very important star dies,

329
00:15:30,631 --> 00:15:33,133
and Dhianelia,
she gets really sad.

330
00:15:33,133 --> 00:15:34,843
NILVAL: Do you know the name
of this star?

331
00:15:34,843 --> 00:15:36,011
‐ Oh, no.

332
00:15:36,011 --> 00:15:39,139
<i>[soft instrumental music]</i>

333
00:15:39,139 --> 00:15:41,642
<i>♪ ♪</i>

334
00:15:41,642 --> 00:15:44,687
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

335
00:15:44,687 --> 00:15:47,481
<i>♪ ♪</i>

336
00:15:47,481 --> 00:15:50,150
PROME: Perhaps the Iron Tribe
and the Silver Tribe

337
00:15:50,150 --> 00:15:52,027
can coexist peacefully.

338
00:15:52,027 --> 00:15:54,321
ROM: No.
They are unstable beings

339
00:15:54,321 --> 00:15:57,199
ruled by irrational thoughts
and emotions.

340
00:15:57,199 --> 00:15:58,659
We must eradicate them

341
00:15:58,659 --> 00:16:01,829
before they develop
into the scourge of our galaxy.

342
00:16:01,829 --> 00:16:04,999
To accomplish this,
we must send multiple Nodos.

343
00:16:04,999 --> 00:16:08,877
PROME: Chaos would ensure
if multiple Nodos were to fight.

344
00:16:08,877 --> 00:16:12,006
A maelstrom of that magnitude
would indeed destroy

345
00:16:12,006 --> 00:16:13,340
an entire race.

346
00:16:13,340 --> 00:16:15,259
ROM: Confrontation
with the fifth Nodos

347
00:16:15,259 --> 00:16:18,345
is a Labor commanded of us
by our predecessors,

348
00:16:18,345 --> 00:16:19,972
the Golden Tribe.

349
00:16:19,972 --> 00:16:22,391
It is unavoidable.

350
00:16:22,391 --> 00:16:24,560
PROME: And if our Nodos
are destroyed?

351
00:16:24,560 --> 00:16:27,354
ROM: We shall leave one behind.

352
00:16:27,354 --> 00:16:29,690
The Labors also dictate
that the other Nodos

353
00:16:29,690 --> 00:16:32,901
are to protect Yuty
of the Silver Tribe.

354
00:16:32,901 --> 00:16:34,236
She stays.

355
00:16:34,236 --> 00:16:37,990
<i>♪ ♪</i>

356
00:16:37,990 --> 00:16:41,076
I agree to destroy
the Iron Tribe.

357
00:16:41,076 --> 00:16:45,748
We'll settle the matter
by sending off multiple Nodos.

358
00:16:45,748 --> 00:16:50,210
Phaetho,
I sense you're disturbed.

359
00:16:50,210 --> 00:16:53,213
I have eliminated
lowly emotions.

360
00:17:00,554 --> 00:17:03,891
‐ Anaesha,
Age's world was made barren.

361
00:17:03,891 --> 00:17:07,227
We must make it bloom
with flowers like these.

362
00:17:07,227 --> 00:17:08,228
<i>[shimmering tones]</i>

363
00:17:08,228 --> 00:17:09,897
‐ Are you all right?

364
00:17:09,897 --> 00:17:11,106
‐ I feel it,

365
00:17:11,106 --> 00:17:13,484
a sudden surge of hostility.

366
00:17:13,484 --> 00:17:14,902
‐ That means...

367
00:17:14,902 --> 00:17:16,695
‐ Yes, Aneasha.

368
00:17:16,695 --> 00:17:18,238
It has begun.

369
00:17:19,156 --> 00:17:20,491
NILVAL: Fire main cannons!

370
00:17:20,491 --> 00:17:23,535
[lasers firing]

371
00:17:25,204 --> 00:17:29,291
Maintain formation and focus
firepower on the advance force.

372
00:17:29,291 --> 00:17:31,085
MELEAGROS: Hold your fire!

373
00:17:31,085 --> 00:17:32,586
Look at that.

374
00:17:34,672 --> 00:17:36,757
<i>[intense music]</i>

375
00:17:36,757 --> 00:17:39,802
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

376
00:17:39,802 --> 00:17:46,850
<i>♪ ♪</i>

377
00:17:52,106 --> 00:17:53,607
[crashing]

378
00:17:56,443 --> 00:17:59,446
[explosions]

379
00:17:59,446 --> 00:18:04,118
<i>♪ ♪</i>

380
00:18:04,118 --> 00:18:07,204
KARKINOS: Bellcross, he stirs.

381
00:18:07,204 --> 00:18:08,956
‐ This is it.

382
00:18:08,956 --> 00:18:11,834
‐ If more than one of us
becomes involved in this battle,

383
00:18:11,834 --> 00:18:13,377
what prevents us from turning
on each other

384
00:18:13,377 --> 00:18:14,795
rather than the fifth?

385
00:18:14,795 --> 00:18:17,172
‐ A confrontation between
more than two members

386
00:18:17,172 --> 00:18:20,175
of the Heroic Tribe has always
been unpredictable.

387
00:18:20,175 --> 00:18:22,136
There is the possibility
that it will end

388
00:18:22,136 --> 00:18:24,138
in unthinkable destruction.

389
00:18:24,138 --> 00:18:26,181
Because of that,
the Silver Tribe is undecided

390
00:18:26,181 --> 00:18:27,725
on the matter.

391
00:18:27,725 --> 00:18:30,602
‐ I would surely give my life
to defeat the fifth Nodos.

392
00:18:30,602 --> 00:18:32,271
Fear is not my nature.

393
00:18:32,271 --> 00:18:34,982
After all,
that was the Labor given to me.

394
00:18:34,982 --> 00:18:37,818
‐ But if you do that,
many stars will die too.

395
00:18:37,818 --> 00:18:39,987
‐ That is why before
that can happen,

396
00:18:39,987 --> 00:18:42,156
you must destroy
Lernaea and I.

397
00:18:42,156 --> 00:18:45,075
‐ If I must...

398
00:18:45,075 --> 00:18:46,160
I will.

399
00:18:50,664 --> 00:18:53,083
BELL NO BELL: This is footage
from three days ago.

400
00:18:53,083 --> 00:18:55,252
‐ They're using this
to demonstrate how brilliant

401
00:18:55,252 --> 00:18:56,754
they are, huh?

402
00:18:56,754 --> 00:19:00,215
The only strategy they have
is using Age as a shield.

403
00:19:00,215 --> 00:19:02,885
‐ I knew they'd try something
like this.

404
00:19:09,349 --> 00:19:12,394
[whooshing]

405
00:19:21,195 --> 00:19:22,488
MELEAGROS: Attention!

406
00:19:24,031 --> 00:19:25,991
We, the mighty Calydonian Fleet,

407
00:19:25,991 --> 00:19:28,494
have finally
reached the solar system.

408
00:19:30,204 --> 00:19:33,332
Planet of the ancient god,
Jupiter.

409
00:19:33,332 --> 00:19:35,084
WOMAN: Oh, look.

410
00:19:35,084 --> 00:19:36,710
It's so bright.

411
00:19:36,710 --> 00:19:39,046
[all speaking indistinctly]

412
00:19:39,046 --> 00:19:40,380
WOMAN: Look at the colors.

413
00:19:40,380 --> 00:19:43,801
‐ At last, we shall make
our triumphant return.

414
00:19:43,801 --> 00:19:48,138
The cradle of all humanity,
our true home.

415
00:19:48,138 --> 00:19:50,015
[alarm blaring]

416
00:19:50,015 --> 00:19:51,892
MAN: Enemy anthills approaching.

417
00:19:51,892 --> 00:19:54,937
[rumbling]

418
00:19:56,647 --> 00:19:57,898
‐ It's massive.

419
00:19:57,898 --> 00:19:59,566
MAN: This is the largest one
on record.

420
00:19:59,566 --> 00:20:01,652
Its offensive capabilities
are unknown.

421
00:20:01,652 --> 00:20:03,237
‐ Those worms!

422
00:20:03,237 --> 00:20:06,573
I'll be damned if we allow them
free reign in our own home!

423
00:20:06,573 --> 00:20:09,493
Big brother, deliver orders
for my Quental Unit

424
00:20:09,493 --> 00:20:10,828
to begin their attack.

425
00:20:10,828 --> 00:20:12,246
‐ There's no need.

426
00:20:12,246 --> 00:20:15,207
We shall let our very own savior
deal with the enemy.

427
00:20:15,207 --> 00:20:18,418
‐ But big brother, it'll damage
our family's reputation

428
00:20:18,418 --> 00:20:19,795
if we do nothing.

429
00:20:19,795 --> 00:20:22,506
‐ Atalantes, do you know
what's missing from

430
00:20:22,506 --> 00:20:24,550
the Yunos royal family?

431
00:20:24,550 --> 00:20:27,594
<i>[intense music]</i>

432
00:20:27,594 --> 00:20:34,601
<i>♪ ♪</i>

433
00:20:37,229 --> 00:20:40,274
[explosions]

434
00:20:40,274 --> 00:20:47,281
<i>♪ ♪</i>

435
00:20:48,532 --> 00:20:49,783
It's simple, really.

436
00:20:49,783 --> 00:20:51,577
All that we're missing
is the one thing

437
00:20:51,577 --> 00:20:55,789
that would make
our family great: a legend.

438
00:20:55,789 --> 00:20:59,168
When we win this holy war
without a single life lost,

439
00:20:59,168 --> 00:21:03,005
they will speak of our great
family for generations to come

440
00:21:03,005 --> 00:21:05,007
as the chosen bloodline.

441
00:21:05,007 --> 00:21:08,135
That legend will aid
in our family's dominion

442
00:21:08,135 --> 00:21:09,720
over the entire galaxy.

443
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:13,265
The Nodos is simply a tool
to accomplish that.

444
00:21:13,265 --> 00:21:15,142
‐ You're so brilliant.

445
00:21:15,142 --> 00:21:17,144
‐ How ridiculous.

446
00:21:17,144 --> 00:21:24,151
<i>♪ ♪</i>

447
00:21:27,154 --> 00:21:28,363
‐ Oh, Age.

448
00:21:28,363 --> 00:21:30,324
<i>♪ ♪</i>

449
00:21:30,324 --> 00:21:31,867
ROM: We have made a decision.

450
00:21:31,867 --> 00:21:36,580
<i>♪ ♪</i>

451
00:21:36,580 --> 00:21:37,998
YUTY: It's decided.

452
00:21:37,998 --> 00:21:40,000
More than one of you
shall fight.

453
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,210
‐ Yes.
I'll go.

454
00:21:41,210 --> 00:21:43,295
YUTY: Lecty.

455
00:21:43,295 --> 00:21:44,630
MEHITAK: I'm going too.

456
00:21:44,630 --> 00:21:46,173
<i>♪ ♪</i>

457
00:21:46,173 --> 00:21:47,466
LECTY: But why?

458
00:21:47,466 --> 00:21:49,718
<i>♪ ♪</i>

459
00:21:49,718 --> 00:21:51,178
‐ All of you will go.

460
00:21:51,178 --> 00:21:53,472
Karkinos and Lecty
will battle him.

461
00:21:53,472 --> 00:21:56,725
And if that isn't good enough,
then Mehitak will join in.

462
00:21:56,725 --> 00:22:00,479
And don't worry,
I'll stop whoever loses control.

463
00:22:00,479 --> 00:22:07,486
<i>♪ ♪</i>

464
00:22:34,179 --> 00:22:37,182
‐ [growling]

465
00:22:37,182 --> 00:22:38,642
<i>♪ ♪</i>

466
00:22:38,642 --> 00:22:41,645
<i>["Azurite" by Tae Urakabe]</i>

467
00:22:41,645 --> 00:22:44,731
[woman singing in Japanese]

468
00:22:44,731 --> 00:22:51,738
<i>♪ ♪</i>

469
00:23:49,629 --> 00:23:53,050
DHIANEILA: Their foolish
behavior enrages the stars

470
00:23:53,050 --> 00:23:55,719
next time on "Heroic Age"
episode 12:

471
00:23:55,719 --> 00:23:58,388
"The Torch of Destruction."

